# Netlify Deployment Plan

## Goal Description
The user wants to deploy the updated "janus-systems" project to Netlify. This involves building the production assets and deploying them to a Netlify site.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration

#### [NEW] [netlify.toml](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/janus-systems/netlify.toml)
- Added to handle SPA routing (redirecting all non-file requests to [index.html](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/janus-systems/index.html)).

### Build Process
- Run `npm run build` to generate the `dist` folder.
- The `dist` folder will contain the static assets ready for deployment.

### Deployment Process
- Use Netlify's manual deploy or CLI to upload the `dist` folder.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Once deployed, visit the Netlify URL provided by the user or generated by the CLI.
- Check that the landing page loads and the hero animation is present.
- Verify that sub-routes (if any) or page refreshes don't return 404s.
